docs.abstract: A meeting in May was meant for a discussion of foreign meddling in this year’s midterm elections. But some tech officials left frustrated.
docs.snippet: A meeting in May was meant for a discussion of foreign meddling in this year’s midterm elections. But some tech officials left frustrated.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Eight of the tech industry’s most influential companies, in anticipation of a repeat of the Russian meddling that occurred during the 2016 presidential campaign, met with United States intelligence officials last month to discuss preparations for this year’s midterm elections.

headline.main: Top Tech Companies Met With Intelligence Officials to Discuss Midterms
headline.print_headline: To Deter Midterm Meddling, U.S. Met With Tech Giants

docs.abstract: Google and Facebook are struggling to catch up with Twitch, a service that Amazon bought four years ago for $1.1 billion.
docs.snippet: Google and Facebook are struggling to catch up with Twitch, a service that Amazon bought four years ago for $1.1 billion.
docs.lead_paragraph: Late on a recent night, more than 600,000 people watched one of the most popular video game players, Tyler Blevins, engage in Fortnite Battle Royale with a celebrity guest: Drake.

headline.main: With Twitch, Amazon Tightens Grip on Live Streams of Video Games
headline.print_headline: Amazon Tightens Grip on Video Game Live Streaming

docs.abstract: Microsoft workers objected to the company’s work with immigration authorities, part of a wave of outrage over the Trump administration’s immigration policy.
docs.snippet: Microsoft workers objected to the company’s work with immigration authorities, part of a wave of outrage over the Trump administration’s immigration policy.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — In an open letter posted to Microsoft’s internal message board on Tuesday, more than 100 employees protested the software maker’s work with Immigration and Customs Enforcement and asked the company to stop working with the agency, which has been separating migrant parents and their children at the border with Mexico.

headline.main: Microsoft Employees Protest Work With ICE, as Tech Industry Mobilizes Over Immigration

docs.abstract: The acquisition of the software development company is meant to help Microsoft gain ground in the area of so-called cloud computing.
docs.snippet: The acquisition of the software development company is meant to help Microsoft gain ground in the area of so-called cloud computing.
docs.lead_paragraph: Microsoft, fully embracing a model it once saw as a threat, said on Monday that it was buying GitHub, an open software platform used by 28 million programmers, for $7.5 billion.

headline.main: Microsoft Buys GitHub for $7.5 Billion, Moving to Grow in Coding’s New Era
headline.print_headline: Deal Lifts Microsoft As It Woos Developers
